## Introduction/Task
In this chapter we guide you through the process of building quite an advanced and more complex template. You are going to re-build *invoice.itx *which is found in the directory from which this tutorial has been opened under *Template Designer directory&gt;/Documentation/en/chapter_8/INFINICA Mobile*. Therefore, create a directory where you save all of the example resources. Copy all .PNG, .XML and .XSD files from */Documentation/en/chapter_8/components *to your new directory.

## Preparations: Template Parts
### Advertising Template Parts
Create a new *Template Part Package *and save it as invoice_templateparts.itx. Create a *Template Part *within invoice_templateparts.itx and name it ad_private. Create another one and name it ad_business. To do so, drag *Template Part *elements from the Palette to the *Template Parts *node in the *Outline View*.

Insert a Block into the *Content *node of ad_private. Enter a *Leader *into the Block and apply the following *properties*:

- Leader

Type: rule

- Style: solid

- Thickness: 0.2 mm

- *Advanced &gt; Leader and Rule &gt; leader-length: *100%

- Block, containing the Leader

Advanced &gt; Block and Line &gt; text-align: justify

Insert another Block below the first one (or simply press ENTER) and set alignment to center. Drag an *Image *element into the second Block. Double click the placeholder and select ad_private.png which you copied to your templates directory. Apply the following properties to the *Image*:

- Width: 10.0 cm

- Height: 3.74 cm

- Scaling: uniform `[15: Therefore, click on the button with the associated chain]`

Press ENTER while the cursor is set after the image element to insert a third block below. Enter some advertising text into the block – e.g.: Have you already heard of Infinica MegaFUN? Check [www.infinicahighspeed.net](http://www.infinicahighspeed.net/) for more information `[16: if you copy that text, style information, might be copied as well. Make sure, you reset these font-style properties in the Advanced property sheet or paste the clipboard’s content into some text editor and copy it again, in order to delete any style information, before inserting.]`

Create another *Block *alike the first one containing a *Leader *element after the just entered text.

Now copy the content of your first *Template Part *(ad_private) to the second one (ad_business) and exchange the image to ad_business.png by either changing the value of *Advanced&gt; Miscellaneous &gt; src *or by double clicking the image and choosing the file from your templates folder. Exchange the marketing text to something else – e.g.:

Have you already discovered Infinica UltraFON? Our business relation center will supply you with information and your customized solution 24/7. For instant information, check [www.infinicahighspeed.net!](http://www.infinicahighspeed.net/)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 22. Template Part Package: invoice_templateparts.itx including the ads*

### Header and Footer template parts
Now we are going to create the template parts for the header and the footer of the template in the same template part package. Of course, if you wanted to separate the ads from the header and footer template parts, you could also create another template part package just for those and import it later into your template with the other one.

#### Header
Create a *Template Part *and call it header. Enter a *Block *into the *Template Part Contents *node and apply *Font size *8 pt. Drag a *Table *into the *Block *and apply the following width to the table columns through the *Advanced Properties &gt; Table &gt; column-width:*

- Column 1: 125 mm

- Column 2: 25 mm

- Column 3: 40 mm

Insert three additional rows to get a total of five. Merge the second and third cell of the first, fourth and fifth row (*Merge with &gt; right cell *in the context menu). Insert an *Image *element into the merged cell of the first row and assign it to infinicamobile_logo.png. Apply the following *properties*:

- Width: 65 mm

- *Advanced &gt; Area Dimension &gt; scaling: *uniform 

Now enter contact information into the table lines:

- 2nd row

2nd column: Service Hotline

- 3rd column: random phone number, e.g.: +49 12345789-0

set *alignment *to right

- 3rd row

2nd column: Service Fax

- 3rd column: random fax number, e.g.: +49 12345789-1

set *alignment *to right

- 4th row

2nd column: random email address, e.g.: billing@infinica-mobile.com

set *alignment *to right

- 5th row

2nd column: random URL, e.g.: [www.infinica-mobile.com](http://www.infinica-mobile.com/)

set *alignment *to right

Insert a second Block below the first one and drag a Leader into it. Apply these properties (Properties &gt; Leader &gt;):

- Type: rule

- Length: 100% `[17: A leader with a percentage as length is barely displayed in the Designer View, as it is not yet certain how long it will be.]`

- Style: solid

#### Footer
Create a *Template Part *and call it footer. Enter a *Block *into the *Template Part Contents *node and enter the following text to it (remember to delete copied style information if necessary!): Infinica Mobile Austria Inc, Box 1234, A-1234 Some City, Office: Some Street 123, A-1234 Some City, FN 123456789

Press ENTER and type the following text into the just created block: Banking details: Infinica Bank, Account # 123456, Bank Code 1234, IBAN AT45678, BIC INFINICATWW

Select the two created blocks and set the font colour to dark grey, e.g. via *Fonts &gt; Font Color*.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 23. Template Part Package including header and footer*

# Preparations: Styles
Create a new Style package, name it invoice_styles.itx and save it to your new directory. Go to the *Styles Packages Node/View*. `[18: Normally the defined Style Packages are available via their own view. However, when the view is closed, the Style Packages node becomes available in the Outline View. In order to show them in a separate view again, just perform a right click on the node in the Outline View and select Open in separate view. This doesn’t only go for the Style Packages node, but for nearly all nodes you find in the Outline View. So if you need to access any node quite often, you can always put it into a separate view so that you don’t have to scroll up and down in the Outline View all the time. For example, you could separate the node Template Parts in case you were going to drag and drop a lot of template parts into your template.]` You should see a style package named (unnamed). Rename it to stylePackage, e.g. by pressing F2 or via the context menu. Then create the following new styles inside the style package by right clicking on the just renamed node and selecting *Add new Style*. Also set the properties as described `[19: The properties are listed according to their names in the advanced property sheet. In order to apply them, just select the style and set the properties like for any other element.]:`

#### base_font
- *Font &gt; font-size: *9 pt

#### small_font
- *Font &gt; font-size: *10 pt

#### small_bold_font
- *Font &gt; font-size: *10 pt

- *Font &gt; font-weight: *bold

#### bold headline
- *Font &gt; font-weight: *bold

- *Font &gt; font-size: *18 pt

- *Font &gt; font-weight: *bold

#### grey_background
- *Font &gt; font-weight: *bold

- *Advanced &gt; Border, Padding, and Background &gt; background-color: *rgb(192,192,192)

Create a new Page Master Package, name it invoice_pagemaster.itx and save it to the other files. Open the *Page Masters *dialog, e.g. by double clicking on the pre-defined entry *A4 *in the *Outline View*. Select the option *Double Sided *and apply the settings as shown in the figures below.

## Creating the Template
### New Template
Create a new *Infinica Template *and save it to the other files in your working directory.

### Imports
Import the three packages created before by either selecting *Add new… *in the context menu of the *External Resources *node or by dragging and dropping *Infinica Template *from the *Palette *to *External Resources *and selecting one of the resources created before. Do this for all three files invoice_templateparts.itx, invoice_styles.itx and invoice_pagemaster.itx. Right after you imported the *Page Master *package, the *Problems *view should display an error message, saying that the Page Master name (A4) is already in use. That’s because your new template

already comes with a Page Master named *A4*, which has the same name as the *Page Master *you defined before in the *Page Master Package *invoice_pagemaster.itx. If you try to generate a PDF preview of the template now, it will fail due to this problem. In order to solve this issue, you could either just rename your local page master, or delete it. Since we are not going to need the local page master anyway, we are going to delete it. In order to do so, go to the *Outline View *and expand the node Page Masters. You should see two Page Masters with the same name now. Try to delete any of them, e.g. via the context menu. If the delete function isn’t available for one of the Page Masters, this means that one is the external one, which is defined in the Page Master package, so you have to delete the other one. `[20: Note that it’s not possible to edit any content of external resources directly in a template that just refers to it. So if you would like to change the Page Master (or anything else that comes from another Infinica Template package) you have to open and edit the external package itself.]`

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 26. Imports of external resources*

Go to the *Style Packages view/node *and drag the base_font style to the *Page Sequence *node. That way you inherit the specified font settings to all its child nodes. Open the *Data Inputs *View and create a new *Data Input ![](data:image/png;base64,)*. Name it xml1, use invoice.xsd as *Schema *and invoice.xml as *XML file.*

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 27. Add new data input*

### Document Header
Create a *Static Page Content *by right clicking the node *A4 (Page Sequence)*. Choose header from the upcoming dialog.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 28. Static Page Content - header and footer*

Delete the *Block *element within the *Static Page Content *header. Create a *Template Part Reference *within the *Static Page Content *and press F2 or select *Rename *in the context menu and type header. The *Template Part *created before and its content respectively are displayed in the template.

### Document Footer
Do the same for the footer. Create a *Static Page Content*, choose footer and insert a *Template Part Reference *assigned to the footer *Template Part*.

Create a *Block *above the *Template Part Reference*, type Page into the *Block *and insert a *Page Number *element from the *Palette*. Through *Advanced &gt; Miscellaneous &gt; page number: current *or *last *you can choose, if the number of the current or the last page will be shown.

Set the text alignment of the *Block *to center and set *Properties &gt; Distances &gt; Margin &gt; bottom: *2 mm. Drag the small_font style to the recently created *Block *in the *Outline View*.

### Global Variables
Create the following global variables with particular content in the *Outline View *through the context menu or by dragging *Variable *elements to the *Global Variables *node:

- basefee - $xml1/invoice/calldetails/amount

- currentfee - sum($xml1/invoice/calldetails/connection/provider/cost)

- tax - $xml1/invoice/calldetails/tax

### The First Page
Enter INVOICE into the first empty block in the *Design Window *and drag the headline style from the *Style View *to the block in the *Outline View*. Apply a margin to the *Block*:

- *Properties &gt; Distances &gt; Margins &gt; Bottom: *25 mm

or

- *Properties &gt; Advanced &gt; Margin &gt; margin-bottom: *25 mm

Insert a second block by pressing ENTER or drag a *Block *element from the *Palette *to the *Outline View*. Drag the small_font_ style to the second block `[21: Previous assigned styles are overwritten by newly applied styles.]` and set *Properties &gt; Distances &gt; Margins &gt; Bottom: *10 mm. Insert a table and apply the following column widths via *Properties &gt; Advanced &gt; Table column-width*:

- Column 1: 125 mm

- Column 2: 25 mm

- Column 3: 40 mm

Delete the second table row and fill the table with the content as shown in the figure below.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 29. Content of address table*

Apply the bold style on the text elements. You can change the date formatting of the dynamic value billingdate by selecting the value in the *Design View *and applying following properties:

- *Properties &gt; Dynamic Value &gt; Formatting: *Date

- *Properties &gt; Dynamic Value &gt; Pattern: *[D01].[M01].[Y]

The values in the square brackets relate to the date, the values outside of the square brackets are directly output. D = day, M = month and Y = year. 01 means that a zero will be inserted in front of a single-digit number.

Insert a new *Block *after your table and create another *Table *with the same layout column- wise and eight rows. Create the structure of the table row as shown below. Drag the small_font style to the recently created *Block *in the *Outline View *and set *Properties &gt; Distances &gt; Margins &gt; Bottom: *10 mm. You can also apply some background colour to the first row through *Properties &gt; Advanced &gt; Border, Padding, and Background &gt; background- color*.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*Figure 30. Table contents (Abbreviated texts: Row 2: EURO excl. sales tax, Row 3: Mobile phone network, Row 8: TOTAL INVOICING AMOUNT)*

Apply borders (border thickness 0.3 mm), distances and formatting to the table as shown in the figure below using the *Border *and *Distance *properties sheets and alignment properties. Number formatting is described at the end of this chapter.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 31. Borders and spacing as desired in the output*

You may change the date formatting of the dynamic values billingdata/from, billingdata/to and due-date by selecting the values in the design view and applying the following properties:

- *Properties &gt; Dynamic Value &gt; Formatting: *Date

- *Properties &gt; Dynamic Value &gt; Pattern: *[D01].[M01].[Y]

Insert a new block after the table and start typing the following text. Insert *Dynamic Values *as shown below. Either drag the nodes from the *Data Input View *to your *Design Window *or enter the *Dynamic Values *manually.

After having typed the first paragraph press ENTER. A new block is automatically created. When all text is entered apply spacing on the just created second block:

- *Properties &gt; Distances &gt; margin-top: *10 mm

- *Properties &gt; Distances &gt; margin-bottom: *10 mm

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*Figure 32. Text and dynamic values*

Drag a *Condition *element below the last block containing *See next page for details! *in the *Outline View*. Input $xml1/invoice/customer/iscompany='false' into the upcoming dialog. Create a second *Condition Branch *using the context menu of the *Condition *node in the *Outline View*, leave the input field blank and just confirm by pressing ENTER or clicking the OK button. Thus an *otherwise*-branch is created.

Add a *Template Part Reference *to the first *Condition Branch *and type ad_private into it. Add a *Template Part Reference *to the second (*otherwise*-) *Condition Branch *and name it ad_business.

You just have finished the first page. Switch to the *PDF (FOP) *preview tab and check your output. It should just look like the figure below.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 33. PDF preview, page 1*

### The Second Page
Create a new *Block *below the *Condition *and apply the following properties to it:

- *Advanced &gt; Keeps and Breaks &gt; break-before: *page

- *Advanced &gt; Margin &gt; margin-top: *25 mm

- *Advanced &gt; Margin &gt; margin-bottom: *5 mm

Drag the small_bold_font style to the currently created Block in the *Outline View*. Create a table within the *Block *and apply the following widths to the columns:

- *Advanced &gt; Table &gt; column-width: *13 cm

- *Advanced &gt; Table &gt; column-width: *3 cm

- *Advanced &gt; Table &gt; column-width: *3 cm

![](data:image/png;base64,)Merge the second cell of the second row with the third cell. Create the following structure as shown in the figure below.

*Figure 34. Second page, first table (shortened text: CONNECTION DETAILS, INFINICA MOBILE + 43 123)*

Apply background colour, borders and distances to the table, as shown in the figure below. Use a border width of 0.3 mm.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 35. Second page, first table layout*

You can change the date formatting of the dynamic values billingdata/from and billingdata/to by selecting the values in the *Design *or *Outline *view and applying following properties:

- *Properties &gt; Dynamic Value &gt; Formatting: *Date

- *Properties &gt; Dynamic Value &gt; Pattern: *[D01].[M01].[Y]

Create a new *Block*, set *Advanced &gt; Margin &gt; margin-bottom: *10 mm and insert a *Table *with four columns and three rows and set the following column widths via *Advanced &gt; Table &gt; column-width*:

- Column 1: 3 cm

- Column 2: 9 cm

- Column 3: 4 cm

- Column 4: 3 cm

Merge the first cell of the first row with the second cell. Apply *Properties &gt; Border &gt; border bottom *to the first and the second row of the table. Border width: 0.3 mm and enter the content as shown on the following figure. Drag the bold style to the first and third row of the table in the *Outline View.*

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 36. Second page, second table structure (shortened text: Services provided by Infinica Mobile:)*

Enter a Block below and type the text Connections into it. Apply the bold style to that block by dragging it from the *Style View *to the *Block*. Create one more *Block *and a table with 5 columns using the following column widths which are applied via *Advanced &gt; Table &gt; column-width*:

- Column 1: 3 cm

- Column 2: 6 cm

- Column 3: 4 cm

- Column 4: 3 cm

- Column 5: 3 cm

Set *Advanced &gt; Margin &gt; margin-bottom: *5 mm on the *Block *containing the table and apply the structure and content to the table as shown in the figure below.

Add a *Repeat*`[22: For more information about the use of the Repeat element see the user guide]` by choosing *Wrap with repeat *in the context menu on the row node. Then enter

$xml1/invoice/calldetails/connection/provider Insert simple *Dynamic Value *elements to the cells with the following values:

- calls

- name

- duration

- $tax `[23: Since this value (VAT) is the same for all rows in this example, we are using the global variable tax here. This variable holds an absolute path which “breaks” the repeat and refers to exactly the node which is specified in the variable. Of course, instead of referring to the variable, you could also put the absolute path directly into the Dynamic Value.]`

- cost

Using the *Properties &gt; Border *apply bottom border to the row in the *Table Header *and top border to the last (second) row in the *Table Body*. Border width: 0.3 mm. Drag the bold style to the first and third row of the table in the *Outline View*.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 37. Page 2, second table structure*

Insert a last *Block, *set *Advanced &gt; Margin &gt; margin-bottom: *10 mm insert *Table *after your *calldetails *table. Apply the following column widths the same way you did it before in the other tables:

- Column 1: 13 cm

- Column 2: 3 cm

- Column 3: 3 cm

Apply the style bold on the header and input the following content:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 38. Second page, last table (shortened text: Total Infinica Mobile +43 123)*

Apply *border top *and *border bottom *to the second row in the table. Also set distances and formatting to the table, as shown in the figure below.

*Figure 39. Borders and spacing as desired in the output*

To modify the formatting (e.g. separators, number of decimal points, etc.) of the dynamic numerical values ($amount, $currentfee + $basefee, etc.) proceed as following. By default, for the decimal separator a period (.) and for the thousands separator a comma (,) is used. `[24: For more information about the default settings see the user guide.]`

Create a new decimal format by selecting *Add new Decimal Format *in the context menu of the *Decimal Formats *node.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 40. define new decimal format*

Modify the desired properties (e.g. another group separator) by selecting the new created decimal format.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 41. adapt the decimal format*

Select a dynamic value in the *Design View *and apply the following properties:

- *Properties &gt; Dynamic Value &gt; Formatting: *Number

- *Properties &gt; Dynamic Value &gt; Pattern: *desired formatting (see examples below)

- *Properties &gt; Dynamic Value &gt; Format: *name of the decimal format

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 42. format the dynamic value*

Possible formats, e.g.:

- 1 decimal point: #.#

- 2 decimal points: #.##

- 2 zeros (also without a decimal point): #.00

After the final table type the text: Thank you for trusting Infinica Mobile and for being our customer!

Switch to the PDF (FOP) preview. The following two pages should be the output of your PDF preview.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

### In case of problems…
... try the following:

- Are the XSD and XML set correctly?

- Are the images and the image source paths set correctly?

- Check the *Problem View*
